President Obama has selected Mr. Joseph Clancy to serve as the permanent director of the United States Secret Service. Clancy, a 27-year veteran of the agency, has served as the Acting Director since October 1st of last year. He has demonstrated strong leadership and credibility within the agency, and has implemented reforms that were recommended by an outside panel. The White House is pleased with his leadership and hopes that he will continue to implement necessary reforms. The press briefing also touched on other topics such as the Iran nuclear talks, the immigration lawsuit, the DHS funding debate, and the Summit on Countering Violent Extremism.